Jenni Evans, News24 Two cyclists were injured when a car crashed into them on the N12 near Potchefstroom. (Supplied: ER24) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Johannesburg - Two cyclists were injured, one critically, when a car crashed into them on the N12 near Potchefstroom on Tuesday, paramedics said. Both men were found lying on the side of the road, about 5km outside the town, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said. One of their bicycles was wedged in front of the car. One man sustained numerous injures and needed advanced life support. The other cyclist sustained minor injuries. They were taken to Potchefstroom Provincial Hospital. The driver of the car was not injured, and local authorities would investigate.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  